14 allocated each fiscal year.
15 3. Except as otherwise provided in subsection 4:
16 (a) An agency which provides child welfare services that receives a grant
17 pursuant to subsection 1 must use the money allocated only for costs associated
18 with the adoption assistance program.
19 (b) Any money from the grant awarded pursuant to subsection 1 that has not
20 been used or committed for expenditure by the agency which provides child welfare
21 services by the end of the fiscal year reverts to the State General Fund.
22 4. The portion of any money remaining at the end of a fiscal year from a grant
23 awarded pursuant to subsection 1 that is identified as savings pursuant to the
24 calculation required under 42 U.S.C. § [673(a)(8)(D)(ii)] 673(a)(8)(A) does not
25 revert to the State General Fund and may be carried forward to the next 2 fiscal
26 [year] years and used for any costs of providing child welfare services [without
